Martha Goldberg Aronson: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 26, 2017 5:43 AM ET
Healthcare Equipment and Supplies

Company Overview of Cardiovascular Systems, Inc.



SnapshotPeople 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Martha Goldberg Aronson  Independent Director, Cardiovascular Systems, Inc.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 7 different industries.See Board Relationships50--
Background

		Ms. Martha Goldberg Aronson served as an Executive Vice President and President of Global Healthcare at Ecolab Inc. from September 2012 to April 2016. Ms. Aronson has nearly 20 years of health care experience. She served as the President of North America and Senior Vice President of Hill-Rom Holdings, Inc. from August 2, 2010 to May 2012. She oversaw all aspects of a $1 billion business. Prior to Hill-Rom, she spent 18 years at Medtronic, Inc. She served as the Chief ... Talent Officer and Senior Vice President of Medtronic, Inc., (alternate name Medtronic plc) since March 2008. She joined Medtronic, Inc. in 1991, first working in corporate development and strategic planning as a business analyst. At Medtronic, Inc., Ms. Aronson served as Vice President of Investor Relations from May 2006 to March 2008, Vice President of the Neurological, Gastroenterology/Urology, Obesity Management, ENT/Neurologic Technology and Diabetes businesses in Western Europe from May 2003 to May 2006 and Vice President and General Manager of Medtronic Gastroenterology/Urology from 2001 to May 2003. She served as corporate officer for Medtronic, Inc. Ms. Aronson also held several managerial positions at Medtronic in marketing and product management. She was an Associate Consultant at Bain & Company, Inc. She has been Independent Director of Cardiovascular Systems, Inc. since February 21, 2017. She has been a Director of CONMED Corporation since February 23, 2016 and Methode Electronics, Inc. since April 19, 2016. She serves as a Director of the Guthrie Theater. She served as an Independent Director at Hutchinson Technology Inc. from June 2010 to October 5, 2016. She is a Member of the Minnesota Women's Economic Roundtable and the Wellesley College Business Leadership Council and serves on the boards of the Minnesota Opera and the Minneapolis Club. She has received a number of awards and accolades throughout her professional career for her outstanding leadership skills and accomplishments in the health care industry, including being named as one of the 35 most influential women in health care in Minnesota in 2014. Ms. Aronson received her MBA from the Harvard Graduate School of Business Administration and a Bachelor of Arts in Economics from Wellesley College.Read Full Background




