Background




Aronson, Martha Goldberg was born on September 20, 1967 in Minneapolis. Daughter of Stanley Morton and Luella Gross Goldberg.
					
					



Education


	 		
			

			Bachelor of Science in Economics, Wellesley College, 1989. Master of Business Administration, Harvard University, 1995.
			
       			












Career


	 		
			Associate consultant Bain & Company, Boston, 1989-1991. Joined Medtronic, Inc., since 1991, product line manager Boston, 1995-1996, business analyst Minneapolis, 1991-1993, director marketing Boston, 1996-1997, United States business director Minneapolis, 1997-2000, general manager, since 2000, vice president, neurological, gastroenterology, urology, obesity management, ENT, neurologic technical, diabetes business, Western Europe, 2003—2006, vice president, Investor Relations, 2006—2008, senior  vice president, chief talent officer, since 2008. Director Transneuronix, Mount Arlington, New Jersey, since 2001.
			
       			












Membership


			Member national and executive committee Friends of Wellesley (Massachusetts) College Athletics, since 1992.
			
    			







Connections


